About PIP ()
    pip is the standard package manager for Python.It allows you to 
    install and manage additional packages that are not part of the
    Python standard library.The concept of a package manager might be
    familiar other languages.
        * PHP uses Composer
        * JavaScript uses npm for package management,
        * Ruby uses gem, and
        * .NET use NuGet.
    In Python, pip has become the standard package manager.pip has been
    included with the Python installer since versions 3.4 for Python 3
    and 2.7.9 for Python 2.

PIP commands:

    *pip help
    *pip list
    *pip install <packagename>
    *pip uninstall <packagename>
    *pip upgrade <packagename>
    *pip show <packagename>
    *python -m pip install --upgrade pip
        C:\Users\user\AppData\Local\Programs\Python\Python39\Lib\site-packages

Step 4:
    Install Django
        * pip install django

    Install Specific Version
        * pip install django==3.1.5

    Upgrade New Version
        * pip install django --upgrade

    Uninstall Django
        * pip uninstall django

    Show Package Information
        * pip show django

    Django Check Version
        * python -m django --version

Step 5:
Create new project
    command:- django-admin startproject projectname

Run project
    command:- python manage.py runserver

Run server on different port
    command:- python manage.py runserver 8000